NATION IN BRIEF; 
OHIO; 
FOUR ARE INJURED IN CRASH OF TRAINS 
An Amtrak train carrying about 220 passengers broadsided a CSX freight train 
near Upper Sandusky, Ohio, injuring four people. Two Amtrak crew members 
remained hospitalized. An Amtrak engineer and a 76-year-old passenger were 
treated and released. The 116-car freight train carried carbolic acid, but none 
of the cargo spilled, a CSX Transportation spokeswoman said. The accident 
occurred when the Amtrak's Broadway Limited train hit the freight train at a 
crossing, an Amtrak spokeswoman said. The cause of the accident was under 
investigation. 
